description:
Johann Christian Fischer (c. 1733 – 29 April 1800) was a German composer and oboist, one of the best-known oboe soloists in Europe during the 1770s.

Michael Niesemann (Oboist) with Kolner Akademie conducted by Michael Alexander Willens

00:00 Allegro
07:35 Andante
12:52 Rondeaux

The Four Seasons, Spring - Francois Boucher (1755)

Enjoy the work.

Julian
